<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0db4646f-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s1708"><num value="1708">§ 1708.</num><heading> Jurisdiction of district courts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The appropriate district court of the United States shall have and exercise jurisdiction of proceedings instituted under <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s1706">section 1706 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0db46470-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/380/tII/s209">Pub. L. 93–380, title II, § 209</ref>, <date date="1974-08-21">Aug. 21, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/516">88 Stat. 516</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0db46471-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id0db46472-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id0db46473-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on and after sixtieth day after <date date="1974-08-21">Aug. 21, 1974</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/93/380/s2/c">section 2(c) of Pub. L. 93–380</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s1221–1">section 1221–1 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
